        <updateDate>2007-07-30T20:15:54Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Medicare Part D Drug Class Protection Act of 2007 - Amends part D (Voluntary Prescription Drug Benefit Program) of title XVIII (Medicare) of the Social Security Act to require that Medicare prescription drug plans using formularies cover all drugs included in six specified therapeutic categories.</p> <p>Sets forth special requirements for reconsideration of coverage determinations, and appeals for drugs included in such categories.</p> <p>Establishes reporting requirements for drugs in these categories.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Medicare Part D Drug Class Protection Act of 2007</title>
    <titles>
      <item>
        <titleType>Official Title as Introduced</titleType>
        <title>To amend title XVIII of the Social Security Act to require that Medicare prescription drug plans using formularies cover all drugs included in 6 specified therapeutic categories, to establish protective requirements for coverage determinations, reconsiderations, and appeals related to such drugs, and to require annual reports on such determinations, reconsiderations, and appeals.</title>
        <billTextVersionName>Introduced in House</billTextVersionName>
